trans-unit.source: Defines <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationship"></xref> criteria to select part-level or package-level relationships.

<xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationshipSelector> is used by the <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageDigitalSignatureManager.Sign%2A> method of the <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageDigitalSignatureManager> class to specify a list of <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationship> parts to be signed.

<xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationshipSelector> is used by the <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageDigitalSignature.SignedRelationshipSelectors%2A> property of the <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageDigitalSignature> class to obtain a list of <xref:System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationship> parts that have been signed with the given digital signature.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationshipSelector"></xref> class.
The [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_uri](~/includes/tlasharptla-uri-md.md)] of the or the (SourceUri="/") that owns the relationship.
The type of the selectionCriteria, either by relationship or relationship .
The qualification string that is used to select the relationships based on the selectorType.
sourceUri or selectionCriteria is `null`.
The selectorType parameter is not valid.
The selectorType parameter is but selectionCriteria is not a valid [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_xsd](~/includes/tlasharptla-xsd-md.md)] [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_id](~/includes/tlasharptla-id-md.md)].
The sourceUri is not the root ("/") and is also not a valid [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)].

Returns a list of <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationship"></xref> objects that match the defined <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationshipSelector.SourceUri"></xref>, <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationshipSelector.SelectorType"></xref>, and <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationshipSelector.SelectionCriteria"></xref>.
The package from which to select the relationships based on the selection criteria.

A list of relationships that match the selection parameters specified to the <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationshipSelector.#ctor(System.Uri,System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationshipSelectorType,System.String)"></xref> constructor.

Gets the selection criteria specified to the <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationshipSelector.#ctor(System.Uri,System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationshipSelectorType,System.String)"></xref> constructor.

The selection criteria based on the <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationshipSelector.SelectorType"></xref> of <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationshipSelectorType.Id"></xref> or <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationshipSelectorType.Type"></xref> specified to the <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationshipSelector.#ctor(System.Uri,System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationshipSelectorType,System.String)"></xref> constructor.

Gets the <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationshipSelectorType"></xref> specified to the <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationshipSelector.#ctor(System.Uri,System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationshipSelectorType,System.String)"></xref> constructor.

The selector type of <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationshipSelectorType.Id"></xref> or <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationshipSelectorType.Type"></xref> specified to the <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationshipSelector.#ctor(System.Uri,System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationshipSelectorType,System.String)"></xref> constructor.

Gets the root package URI ("/") or part <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart.Uri"></xref> specified to the <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationshipSelector.#ctor(System.Uri,System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationshipSelectorType,System.String)"></xref> constructor as the owner of the relationship.

The root package URI ("/") or part <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.PackagePart.Uri"></xref> specified to the <xref href="System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationshipSelector.#ctor(System.Uri,System.IO.Packaging.PackageRelationshipSelectorType,System.String)"></xref> constructor as the owner of the relationship.
